{"title_page": "June Leow", "text_new": "{{short description|Malaysian politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Liao (surname)|Leow]] {{noitalic|({{linktext|lang=zh|\u5ed6}})}}}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay styles and titles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Other salutations|Puan]]\n| name = June Leow Hsiad Hui\n| native_name = {{nobold|\u5ed6\u4e66\u6167}}\n| native_name_lang = zh-my\n| honorific-suffix = [[Member of Parliament|MP]]\n| image =\n| caption =\n| birth_name = June Leow Hsiad Hui\n| birth_date = {{birth year and age|1964|}} \n| birth_place = \n| residence = [[Rawang, Selangor]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| constituency_MP = [[Hulu Selangor (federal constituency)|Hulu Selangor]], Selangor\n| parliament = Malaysian\n| term_start = 10 May 2018\n| term_end = \n| majority = 13,391 (2018)\n| predecessor = [[P. Kamalanathan|Kamalanathan Panchanathan]] ([[Malaysian Indian Congress|MIC]]-[[Barisan Nasional|BN]])\n| successor = \n| citizenship = [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]]\n| party = [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|PKR]]\u2014[[Pakatan Harapan]]\n| occupation = Politician\n| relations =\n| spouse = Lin Han Qiao (\u6797\u6c49\u4fa8)\n| children = 3\n| website = \n| footnotes = {{pom|3617}}\n}}\n\n'''June Leow Hsiad Hui''' ({{lang-zh|s=\u5ed6\u4e66\u6167|t=\u5ed6\u66f8\u6167|p=Li\u00e0o Sh\u016bhu\u00ec}}, born 1964)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sinchew.com.my/node/1786458 |script-title=zh:\u6211\u7684\u672a\u6765\u4e0d\u662f\u68a6\uff1a\u5ed6\u4e66\u6167\u4e0d\u5f53\u5bcc\u592a\u5f53\u8bae\u5458\uff0e\u76fc\u5728\u4e4c\u96ea\u5efa\u8bbe\u5927\u5b66|date=22 August 2018|publisher=[[Sin Chew Daily]]|language=zh-hans}}</ref> is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician. She is the incumbent [[Dewan Rakyat|Member of Parliament]] for [[Hulu Selangor (federal constituency)|Hulu Selangor]] federal constituency in [[Selangor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.awanireview.com/articles/2018/07/10/news/first-time-mp-june-leow-low-profile-big-win-390/|title=First Time MP June Leow: Low Profile, Big Win|author=Mariam Azmi |publisher=[[Astro Awani|Awani Review]]}}</ref> She is a member of the [[People's Justice Party (Malaysia)|People's Justice Party]] (PKR), a component party of the [[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH) coalition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2018/05/10/pakatan-strengthens-grip-on-selangor-party-secures-41-out-of-56-state-assembly-seats/|title=Pakatan strengthens grip on Selangor - Nation - The Star Online|website=www.thestar.com.my}}</ref> Leow was a councillor in the [[Hulu Selangor District Council]] (MDHS) previously.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/community/2013/11/29/hulu-selangor-councillors-to-be-given-designated-zones-next-year/|title=Hulu Selangor councillors to be given designated zones next year|website=thestar.com.my|date=29 November 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ '''[[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]: P94 [[Hulu Selangor (federal constituency)|Hulu Selangor]], [[Selangor]].'''<ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{Cite web\n  | title = Malaysia General Election \n  | work = undiinfo Malaysian Election Data\n  | publisher = [[Malaysiakini]]\n  | url = http://undi.info/#\n  | accessdate = 4 February 2017}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref name=\"GE14 results\">{{cite web|url=https://keputusan.spr.gov.my/|title=SEMAKAN KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM KE - 14|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay|accessdate=17 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"The Star GE14\">{{cite web|url=https://election.thestar.com.my/|title=The Star Online GE14|publisher=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref> \n!|Year\n!colspan=2|Government \n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!colspan=2|Opposition\n!|Votes\n!|Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|M