ENGANG ABDULLAH SANI TERIMA GELARAN 'DATUK'|date=1 November 2016|publisher=SmasaNews.com|work=Smasa News}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Kuala Langat (federal constituency)]]\n* [[Kapar (federal constituency)]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Selangor-FedRep}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abdullah Sani Abdul Hamid}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:People from Perak]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Malaysian trade unionists]]\n[[Category:People's Justice Party (Malaysia) politicians]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian people]]\n\n\n{{Malaysia-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Bearcat", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:duplicate categorization; already in subcat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdullah_Sani_Abdul_Hamid"}
{"title_page": "Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Malaysian name|Abdul Azeez |Abdul Rahim}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix   = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Datuk Seri|Datuk Seri Panglima]]\n| name = Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim\n| native_name = \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u064a\u0645<br>{{small|\u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb8\u0bc0\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0bb9\u0bc0\u0bae\u0bcd}}\n| honorific-suffix   = {{small| [[Order of Meritorious Service|PJN]] [[Order of Kinabalu#Grand Commander|SPDK]] [[List of post-nominal letters (Malacca)|DCSM]] [[List of post-nominal letters (Pahang)|SSAP]] [[List of post-nominal letters (Pahang)|DIMP]] [[Order of Loyalty to Sultan Abdul Halim Mu'adzam Shah|DHMS]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]] }}\n| image = Azeez Rahim.jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Abdul Azeez bin Abdul Rahim\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1966|11|19}}\n| birth_place = [[Selangor]], Malaysia\n| residence =\n| death_date =\n| death_place = \n| office = Chairperson of [[Tabung Haji]] (TH)\n| term_start = 1 July 2013\n| term_end = 14 May 2018\n| successor = Mohammed Nor Md Yusof\n| predecessor = Abi Musa Asa'ari Mohamed Nor\n| primeminister = [[Najib Razak]] <br /> [[Mahathir Mohamad]]\n| constituency_MP1 = [[Baling (federal constituency)|Baling]]\n| parliament1 = Malaysian\n| term_start1 = 5 May 2013\n| term_end1 = \n| majority1 = 5,185 ([[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]])<br />1,074 ([[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]])\n| predecessor1 = [[Taib Azamudden Md Taib]] ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]]-[[Pakatan Rakyat|PR]])\n| successor1 =\n| party = [[United Malay National Organisation]] (UMNO)\n| otherparty =  [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN)\n| occupation = Politician\n| profession = Businessman\n| spouse = Khadijah Mohd Noor \n| children = 4\n| website = {{url|www.azeezrahim.com}}\n| footnotes =\n}}\n\n[[Malay titles#Datuk Seri|Datuk Seri Panglima]] '''Abdul Azeez bin Abdul Rahim''' ([[Jawi alphabet|Jawi]]: \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u064a\u0645, {{lang-ta|\u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb8\u0bc0\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0baa\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0bb9\u0bc0\u0bae\u0bcd|Aptul as\u012bs pi\u1e49 aptul rah\u012bm}}; born 19 November 1966) is a [[Malaysian people|Malaysian]] politician currently serving as the Member of Parliament (MP) of [[Parliament of Malaysia|Malaysia]] for the seat of [[Baling (federal constituency)|Baling]] in the state of [[Kedah]]. He is a member of [[United Malay National Organisation]] (UMNO), a major component of the [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN) coalition. Due to his [[South Indian]] descent, he speaks fluent [[Tamil language|Tamil]] in addition to Malay and English.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/242959|title=The day Abdul Azeez and Manivannan made history|work=[[Malaysiakini]]|date=4 October 2013|access-date=30 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Government linked companies (glc) and non-governmental organisations (ngo)==\nIn 2011 Abdul Azeez became a director of [[Tabung Haji]] (TH), a Malaysian fund for Muslims to save for the ''[[hajj]]'' pilgrimage. In 2013, after his election to Parliament, he became Tabung Haji's chairman.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/baling-mp-abdul-azeez-is-new-tabung-haji-chair/ |title=Baling MP Abdul Azeez is new Tabung Haji chair |date=2 July 2013 |work=The Malaysian Insider |accessdate=27 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204112405/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/baling-mp-abdul-azeez-is-new-tabung-haji-chair/ |archivedate=4 December 2014 }}</ref> However in 2018, after his reelection as member of parliament and the change of ruling government to [[Pakatan Harapan]] (PH), he resigned as chairman of Tabung Haji.<ref name =\"TH resign\">{{cite news|url=http://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/nation/2018/05/24/azeez-confirms-he-has-quit-tabung-haji-as-chairman/|title=Azeez confirms he has quit as Tabung Haji chairman|date=24 May 2018|work=[[Free Malaysia Today]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nAzeez also founded and headed the Putera 1Malaysia Club (''Kelab Putera 1Malaysia''), a non-government organization that has, among other things, led humanitarian missions to [[Gaza Strip|Gaza]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nst.com.my/node/25442|title=NGO declares Gaza mission a success|date=22 August 2014|work=New Straits Times|accessdate=27 November 2014}}</ref> In 2012 [[Hamas]] appointed him as an honorary ambassador for [[State of Palestine|Palestine]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/abdul-azeez-appointed-honorary-ambassador-for-palestine/ |title=Abdul Azeez appointed honorary ambassador for Palestine |date=13 December 2012 |work=The Malaysian Insider |accessdate=27 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204112515/http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/abdul-azeez-appointed-honorary-ambassador-for-palestine/ |archivedate=4 December 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Political career==\n===Party career===\nAbdul Azeez was elected to UMNO's Supreme Council, the body that governs the party, in 2009. He was the 25th and final candidate elected.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://web10.bernama.com/umno2009/index.php?lang=en&sid=newsdetail&id=399428|title=UMNO Election 2008 Results|date=26 March 2009|agency=Bernama|accessdate=28 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205091355/http://web10.bernama.com/umno2009/index.php?lang=en&sid=newsdetail&id=399428|archive-date=5 December 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was re-elected to the Supreme Council in 2013, this time finishing in seventh place.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2013/10/20/umno-polls-final-results/|title=Umno polls: Results for VP and supreme council|date=20 October 2013|work=The Star|accessdate=28 November 2014}}</ref> He formerly headed \"Putera UMNO\", a group for young members of UMNO when he was the EXCO member of UMNO Youth.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/story/?file=%2f2007%2f2%2f14%2fnation%2f20070214150942&sec=nation|title=35 Putra UMNO members begin parachute training|last=Hamdan Raja Abdullah|date=14 February 2007|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=28 November 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Parliamentary career===\nAzeez was chosen as the [[Barisan Nasional]] (BN) candidate for the seat of [[Baling (federal constituency)|Baling]] at the [[2008 Malaysian general election|2008 election]]. He lost to the [[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party]] (PAS) candidate, [[Taib Azamudden Md Taib]], by 7,613 votes. The state of [[Kedah]] swung back to BN at the [[2013 Malaysian general election|2013 election]], and Azeez, selected again as the BN candidate in Baling, was elected to Parliament.<ref name =\"PRU 2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.pmo.gov.my/election/maklumat.asp?strTahun=2013&strDR=P016&strDUN=0000 |title=Maklumat Terperinci Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum 2013 |publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |accessdate=26 November 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221140117/http://www2.pmo.gov.my/election/maklumat.asp?strTahun=2013&strDR=P016&strDUN=0000 |archivedate=21 December 2014 }}</ref> He was re-elected in the [[2018 Malaysian general election|2018 election]].\n\n==Controversies and issues==\n===Corruption allegations===\nOn 22 May 2018, [[Malaysian Anti-Corruption Commission]] (MACC) raided and seized over RM500,000 in cash of various currencies, some documents, jewellery and luxury watches in several houses and offices in four states occupied by Azeez.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thecoverage.my/news/macc-raid-tabung-haji-chiefs-umno-datuk-seri-abdul-azeez-abdul-rahim-home-seize-rm500000-cash-and-documents/|title=MACC Raid Tabung Haji Chief's UMNO Datuk Seri Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim Home \u2013 Seize RM500,000 Cash And Documents|last=Bythecoverage|date=23 May 2018|work=The Coverage|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2018/05/372281/macc-raids-three-properties-linked-azeez-rahim|title=MACC raids three properties linked to Azeez Rahim|author= Muhammad Mustakim Ramli and Mohd Hasbi Sidek|date=23 May 2018|work=[[New Straits Times]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref> In the midst of MACC investigation, Azeez announced he had tendered his resignation as the Tabung Haji's chairman on 14 May 2018.<ref name =\"TH resign\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2018/05/23/abdul-azeez-resigns-as-tabung-haji-chairman/|title=Abdul Azeez resigns as Tabung Haji chairman|date=23 May 2018|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe MACC arrested Azeez with his elder brother and cousin on 25 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/macc-arrests-baling-mp-azeez-abdul-rahim-%E2%80%94-report-%C2%A0|title=MACC arrests Baling MP Azeez Abdul Rahim \u2013 report |date=25 September 2018|work=[[Malaysiakini]]|publisher=The Edge Markets|accessdate=25 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2018/09/26/graft-investigators-digging-into-abdul-azeezs-past/|title=Graft investigators digging into Abdul Azeez's past|date=26 September 2018|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref> Azeez was released on RM500,000 bail after his 10-day MACC remand ended.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/baling-mp-abdul-azeez-released-rm500000-bail|title=Baling MP Abdul Azeez released on RM500,000 bail |date=5 October 2018|agency=[[Bernama]]|publisher=The Edge Markets|accessdate=5 October 2018}}</ref> But MACC arrested his 24-year-old son the same day he was released.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2018/10/05/baling-mp-abdul-azeez-released-but-his-son-is-arrested/|title=Baling MP Abdul Azeez released \u2013 but his son is arrested|author= Mazwin Nik Anis |date=5 October 2018|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=5 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nTabung Haji on 30 November 2018 reported to police against Azeez as its former chairman and senior management over alleged misuse of RM22&nbsp;million belonging to a charitable fund for politically-linked activities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.malaymail.com/s/1698849/tabung-hajis-ex-chair-azeez-senior-management-named-in-alleged-funds-misuse|title=Tabung Haji's ex-chair Azeez, senior management named in alleged funds misuse probe|author=Ida Lim|date=30 November 2018|work=[[Malay Mail]]|accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe MACC again arrested Azeez and his brother on 15 January 2019 where he was charged with 3 counts of RM 5.2&nbsp;million graft and 9 counts of RM 139.4&nbsp;million money laundering totaling RM 144.6&nbsp;million on the next day.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2019/01/16/baling-mp-claims-trial-to-three-counts-of-graft-involving-rm5point2mil/|title=Abdul Azeez hit with 12 counts of graft and money laundering (Updated)|author= Nurbaiti Hamdan |date=16 January 2019|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 August 2019, Kuala Lumpur Sessions Court set 25 Sep and 11 Oct to hear the corruption case of Azeez and his brother. After Judge Azura Alwi announced the dates, however, Deputy Public Prosecutor Azlinda Ahad said the prosecution will apply to transfer the case to the High Court. Defence lawyer Hisyam Teh Poh Teik did not raise any objection to the prosecution's plan.<ref>https://www.theedgemarkets.com/article/extabung-haji-chairmans-graft-case-hearing-sept-25-oct-11</ref>\n\n==Election results==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin:0.5em ; font-size:95%\"\n|+ [[Dewan Rakyat|Parliament of Malaysia]]: P16 [[Baling (federal constituency)|Baling]], Kedah<ref name =\"PRU 2013\"/><ref name=\"The Star 2008 GE results\">{{Cite web\n |title=Malaysia Decides 2008 \n |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] \n |url=http://thestar.com.my/election/ \n |accessdate=25 January 2010 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409212729/http://thestar.com.my/election/ \n |archivedate=9 April 2008 \n}} Percentage figures are calculated based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"election results\">{{cite web|url=http://semak.spr.gov.my/spr/laporan/5_KedudukanAkhir.php |title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum Parlimen/Dewan Undangan Negeri |publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay |accessdate=4 February 2017 }} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"undiinfo\">{{Cite web  | title = Malaysia General Election   | work = undiinfo Malaysian Election Data  | publisher = [[Malaysiakini]]  | url = http://undi.info/#  | accessdate = 4 February 2017}} Results only available from the [[2004 Malaysian general election|2004 election]].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://resultpru13.spr.gov.my/module/keputusan/paparan/paparan_laporan.php|title=KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM 13|work=Sistem Pengurusan Maklumat Pilihan Raya Umum|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay |accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref><ref name =\"myundi pru 13\">{{cite web |url=http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |title=my undi : Kawasan & Calon-Calon PRU13 : Keputusan PRU13 (Archived copy) |website=myundi.com.my|accessdate=9 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331000718/http://www.myundi.com.my/pru13/region.aspx |archivedate=31 March 2014  }}</ref><ref name=\"Utusan PRU 13 results\">{{cite web|url=http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|title=Keputusan Pilihan Raya Umum ke-13|work=[[Utusan Malaysia]]|accessdate=26 October 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180321134049/http://ww2.utusan.com.my/utusan/special.asp?pr=PilihanRaya2013&pg=keputusan.htm|archive-date=21 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"GE14 results\">{{cite web|url=https://keputusan.spr.gov.my/|title=SEMAKAN KEPUTUSAN PILIHAN RAYA UMUM KE \u2013 14|publisher=[[Election Commission of Malaysia]] |language=Malay |accessdate=17 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref><ref name=\"The Star GE14\">{{cite web|url=https://election.thestar.com.my/|title=The Star Online GE14|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|accessdate=24 May 2018}} Percentage figures based on total turnout.</ref>  \n! Year\n! colspan=2|Government\n! Votes\n! Pct\n! colspan=2|Opposition\n! Votes\n! Pct\n!|Ballots cast\n!|Majority\n!|Turnout\n|-\n|[[2008 Malaysian general election|2008]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim ([[United Malay National Organisation|UMNO]])\n|align=\"right\" |28,461\n|44.10%\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|'''[[Taib Azamudden Md Taib]]''' ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|'''PAS''']])\n|'''36,074'''\n|'''55.90%'''\n|65,764\n|7,613\n|83.47%\n|-\n|[[2013 Malaysian general election|2013]]\n|{{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n|'''Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim''' ([[United Malay National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n|align=\"right\" |'''43,504'''\n|'''53.17%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Najmi Ahmad ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |38,319\n|46.86%\n|83,109\t\n|5185\n|89.20%\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2018 Malaysian general election|2018]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{Party shading/Barisan Nasional}} |\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Abdul Azeez Abdul Rahim''' ([[United Malay National Organisation|'''UMNO''']])\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"right\" |'''38,557'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''42.60%'''\n|{{Party shading/PAS}} |\n|Hassan Saad ([[Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party|PAS]])\n|align=\"right\" |37,48