dul Rahim Bakri}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:People from Sabah]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:Malaysian United Indigenous Party politicians]]\n[[Category:United Malays National Organisation politicians]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Members of the Dewan Rakyat]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Malaysian Friendship and Trade Centre]]\n[[Category:21st-century Malaysian politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Malay name|Abdul Rahim|Bakri}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix = [[Malay titles#Honorary styles|Yang Berhormat]] [[Malay titles#Datuk|Datuk]] [[Hajji|Haji]] \n| name             = Abdul Rahim Bakri\n| native_name = \u0639\u0628\u062f\u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0646 \u0628\u0643\u0631\u064a\n| honorific-suffix = {{small|[[List of post-nominal letters (Malacca)|DMSM]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]]}}\n| image            =\n| caption          =\n| birth_name       = Abdul Rahim bin Bakri\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1961|04|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Crown Colony of North Borneo]] (now [[Sabah]], [[Malaysia]])\n| residence        =\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| office = [[Minister of Finance (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Finance]]\n| primeminister = [[Muhyiddin Yassin]]\n| constituency = [[Kudat (federal constituency)|Kudat]]\n| alongside = [[Mohd Shahar Abdullah]]\n| term_start = 10 March 2020\n| term_end = \n| successor = \n| predecessor = [[Amiruddin Hamzah]]\n| minister = [[Zafrul Aziz|Tengku Zafrul Tengku Abdul Aziz]]\n| monarch = [[Abdullah of Pahang|Abdullah]]\n| office1 = [[Ministry of Defence (Malaysia)|Deputy Minister of Defence]]\n| primeminister1 = [[Najib Razak]]\n| constituency1 = [[Kudat (federal constituency)|Kudat]]\n| term_start1 = 16 May 2013\n| term_end1 = 29 July 2015\n| successor1 = [[Mohd Johari Baharum]]\n| predecessor1 = [[Abdul Latiff Ahmad]]\